mlops: dcterms:description "An upper-level ontology for representing machine learning operations (MLOps) concepts across the ML lifecycle. It provides abstract types for assets, processes, and governance constructs needed to describe ML-enabled systems independent of any specific tool or organization. The ontology is intended to support interoperability, metadata integration, and consistent documentation of ML workflows and artifacts. It aligns with common web and semantic standards (RDF(S), OWL, SKOS, schema.org)." .
mlops:produces rdfs:subPropertyOf schema:result .
