<https://example.com/mlops/mlo/MachineLearningOperationalizationOntology> dcterms:description "The Machine Learning Operationalization Ontology models abstract concepts involved in bringing machine learning models from development into production within ML-enabled software systems. It covers productionalization activities (packaging, integration, telemetry, monitoring, maintenance, retraining, rollout), ML lifecycle automation via pipelines, and the management of ML assets and experiments for provenance and compliance. It also represents socio-technical aspects such as cross-team collaboration among roles involved in MLOps. The ontology is intended to support consistent conceptualization and classification of MLOps practices, processes, and technologies." .
<https://example.com/mlops/mlo/hasActivity> a owl:ObjectProperty .
