mke:MachineKnowledgeEngineeringOntology dcterms:description "This ontology models abstract concepts for engineering, synthesizing, and operationalizing knowledge about machine-learning operations (MLOps) and related lifecycle practices. It captures concepts for evidence sources (academic and gray literature), review methodologies, planning/selection/extraction/synthesis stages, research questions, and the notion of conceptual frameworks and practice snapshots used to organize evolving MLOps practices and challenges. The ontology is intended to support structuring and comparing MLOps knowledge across time, sources, and perspectives, without encoding any specific studies or factual results." .
