<https://example.com/mlops/mlsr#MachineLearningSystemsResearchOntology> dcterms:description "An ontology for representing research processes and methodological concepts used to study machine learning systems and MLOps. It models literature search and selection workflows (e.g., search strings, inclusion/exclusion criteria, quality assessment, snowballing), qualitative analysis practices (e.g., data extraction, coding, code books, themes), and selected MLOps conceptualizations such as continuous engineering practices within an ML lifecycle. The ontology supports describing how evidence is gathered and synthesized and how MLOps-related concepts are organized for reporting and traceability." .
<https://example.com/mlops/mlsr#AcademicDatabase> rdfs:comment "A search source representing curated academic indexing services used for peer-reviewed literature retrieval." .
<https://example.com/mlops/mlsr#StudySelectionProcess> rdfs:subClassOf <https://example.com/mlops/mlsr#ResearchProcess> .
<https://example.com/mlops/mlsr#FeedbackLoop> rdfs:comment "A loop between lifecycle phases that supports iteration and adaptation in ML projects due to their experimental nature." .
<https://example.com/mlops/mlsr#hasThreatToValidity> rdfs:label "has threat to validity" .
<https://example.com/mlops/mlsr#MLLifecycle> rdfs:comment "The lifecycle of an ML-enabled software system, including phases that can be connected via feedback loops and iterative updates." .
<https://example.com/mlops/mlsr#involvesPilotStudy> rdfs:domain <https://example.com/mlops/mlsr#ResearchProcess> .
