<https://example.com/mlops/mlce> dcterms:description "The Machine Learning Continuous Engineering Ontology models abstract concepts and relationships for managing continuous practices across the machine learning lifecycle. It covers project initiation, lifecycle activities (data and model work), automation via pipelines, DevOps-derived practices, cultural and organizational collaboration, and productionalization concerns such as reproducibility, reliability, efficiency, scalability, and responsible practices. The ontology is intended to support semantic integration of MLOps activities, artefacts, roles, and governance requirements in a tool- and organization-agnostic way." .
