<https://example.com/mlops/mlpo> dcterms:description "This ontology models abstract concepts and relationships involved in taking machine learning solutions from development to reliable production operations. It covers model development and assessment (training, evaluation, validation, optimization), deployment patterns (packaging, serving, APIs), monitoring and observability, pipeline automation and triggers, artifact/version/provenance management, quality assurance, and team/role responsibilities. It is intended to support semantic interoperability across MLOps processes, tooling, and documentation by providing a shared vocabulary aligned to standard web vocabularies." .
